{
  "text": "In terms of helminth infections, there is evidence for the Southern European emergence of snail-transmitted fluke infections, including opisthrochiasis in Italy [CITATION_1] , and schistosomiasis in Corsica, off the coast of southern France [CITATION_2] .",
